10 September 2019 The Justice, Crime Prevention and Security (JCPS) Cluster Ministers will hold a media briefing on the recent incidents of public violence  in different parts of South Africa. The cluster will give progress on the work done thus far and also outline the plans that government is implementing to make sure that law and order is restored in the country. The details of the media briefing are as follows: Date: Tuesday, 10 September 2019 TIime:  12:00 Venue:  Imbizo Media Centre, 120 Plein Street, Parliament in Cape Town NB: There will be a video link to Ronnie Mamoepa Media Centre, Tshedimosetso House, Cnr Frances Baard and Festival streets, Hatfield in Pretoria RSVPs: Takalani Mukwevho Cell: 082 227 9308 E-mail: takalanim@gcis.gov.za Enquiries:  Siphiwe Dlamini Cell: 083 645 4294 Issued: Government Communication and Information System